    Tour was good but the overtime experience is a waste of money
    It was fine but not great; 3.5 stars not 4. I guess if you are a big Raiders fan the tour might have been more meaningful. The stadium is new and nicely appointed. The overtime experience is a complete waste of money - dont bother. All it is is an open area with some simple games (cornhole, football toss, cup pong) and one free food item (stale nacho chips and sauce; a very basic hot dog) OR a drink. Not worth the extra $25 in the least.

    Amazing Stadium Tour
    Booked online and arrived an hour early before our slot as the cab was way early but no problem, straight in. Straight away from the parking lot you can see its a magnificent stadium. After our guide Chris had introduced himself and went as always in with the team supporters jokes, and they were very amusing. The tour throughout was very well organised and informative and made extremely interesting by our guide. Unfortunately we couldnt get onto the pitch as it was undergoing removal from the previous days activities. We was informed of this before we booked. With plenty of picture opportunities and info gathered we finished our tour after about seventy minutes. Overall its an awesome experience especially if you visit from abroad and see how a great stadium can be. Definitely worth a visit
